{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/about/kappafeed/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Mike Upchurch","author":"Mike Upchurch"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"9b172b2c-e6ac-59ba-a68a-d0118debf966","excerpt":"What is it? Kappafeed is a program that listens in top Twitch.tv channel chatrooms for whichever emoticon the user has selected, and displays all messages inâ€¦","html":"<h2>What is it?</h2>\n<p>Kappafeed is a program that listens in top <a href=\"http://www.twitch.tv/\">Twitch.tv</a> channel chatrooms for whichever emoticon the user has selected, and displays all messages in one collective feed. It integrates with Twitch APIs and IRC servers in order to merge the top chat channels into one feed.</p>\n<p>I also created a Kappafeed Overwolf app for a contest they were hosting and won a gaming headset. <a href=\"https://github.com/mupchrch/kappafeed_overwolf\">Overwolf app source.</a></p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 656px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4a8d02f0ae6b436ff6fe58e88ac7aaab/065ac/kappafeed-overwolf.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.4%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"The Kappafeed Overwolf app running over League of Legends.\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/4a8d02f0ae6b436ff6fe58e88ac7aaab/065ac/kappafeed-overwolf.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4a8d02f0ae6b436ff6fe58e88ac7aaab/0479a/kappafeed-overwolf.jpg 250w,\n/static/4a8d02f0ae6b436ff6fe58e88ac7aaab/41099/kappafeed-overwolf.jpg 500w,\n/static/4a8d02f0ae6b436ff6fe58e88ac7aaab/065ac/kappafeed-overwolf.jpg 656w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 656px) 100vw, 656px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">The Kappafeed Overwolf app running over League of Legends.</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<h2>What did I learn?</h2>\n<p>I learned a lot about maintaining servers and keeping a service running reliably 24/7. Admittedly, the code for this project got a bit unruly as more features were added and more error handling of edge cases was added. I learned valuable lessons about code refactor and structure for future projects.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/mupchrch/kappafeed\">View the source on Github.</a></p>\n<h3>Technologies</h3>\n<p><em>Python, Tornado Web Server, IRC, Websockets, HTML, JQuery, CSS</em></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"kappafeed","date":"February 02, 2014","description":"A Twitch chat emoji tracker."}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/about/kappafeed/","previous":null,"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/about/et-navswarm/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"ET-NavSwarm"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3296784666","63159454"],"slicesMap":{}}